      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MR MAGNUS (1) will carry the top weight but he deserves to with the form her brings into this. He stuck on well over 1100m at Flemington last start in a good race and this looks to shape nicely on the back of that effort. Jumped favourite in a similar race back in November and has been in better races since. Can see him returning to winning ways. BOLD SUITOR (6) is the new kid on the block with plenty of talent up his sleeve. he was good winning his maiden over this track and trip 21 days ago and this looks to shape nicely again from an inside alley. Will take plenty of catching. BLUE BANDIT (5) resumes here without a trial but he showed good ability through his debut campaign. The inside draw can see him up on the speed for McNeil and a forward showing is on the cards. MY ZEPHYR (7) can improve dropping right back in grade today.",
